        u1_0.updated_at,

        PUBLIC.users u1_0

    create table PUBLIC.addresses (
        is_default boolean,
        created_at timestamp(6),
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        user_id bigint not null,
        address_type varchar(255),
        city varchar(255) not null,
        country varchar(255) not null,
        postal_code varchar(255) not null,
        state varchar(255) not null,
        street_address varchar(255) not null,
        primary key (id)
    )
Hibernate: 
    create table PUBLIC.audit_logs (
        http_status_code INT DEFAULT 200 not null,
        entity_id bigint,
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        timestamp timestamp(6) not null,
        user_id bigint not null,
        error_category VARCHAR(50) DEFAULT 'SUCCESS',
        ip_address varchar(50),
        action varchar(100) not null,
        entity_type varchar(100) not null,
        user_agent varchar(500),
        new_value TEXT,
        old_value TEXT,
        primary key (id)
    )

    create table PUBLIC.cart_items (

        cart_id bigint not null,
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        product_id bigint not null,
        primary key (id)

    create table PUBLIC.categories (
        is_active boolean,
        minimum_stock_threshold integer,
        created_at timestamp(6),
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        description TEXT,
        image_url varchar(255),
        name varchar(255) not null unique,
        primary key (id)
    )
Hibernate: 
    create table PUBLIC.inventory (
        minimum_stock_level integer not null,
        quantity_in_stock integer not null,
        quantity_reserved integer not null,
        use_category_threshold boolean,
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        last_restocked timestamp(6),
        last_threshold_breach timestamp(6),
        product_id bigint not null unique,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        version bigint,
        status varchar(255) not null check (status in ('IN_STOCK','LOW_STOCK','OUT_OF_STOCK')),
        primary key (id)
    )
Hibernate: 
    create table PUBLIC.inventory_threshold_breach_events (
        current_quantity integer not null,
        threshold_level integer not null,
        created_at timestamp(6),
        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        inventory_id bigint not null,
        product_id bigint not null,
        breach_type varchar(255) not null check (breach_type in ('THRESHOLD_BREACH','OUT_OF_STOCK','BACK_IN_STOCK','THRESHOLD_RESTORED')),
        details TEXT,
        new_status varchar(255) not null check (new_status in ('IN_STOCK','LOW_STOCK','OUT_OF_STOCK')),
        primary key (id)
    )

    create table PUBLIC.orders (

        is_deleted boolean,
        shipping_amount numeric(38,2),
        tax_amount numeric(38,2),

        created_at timestamp(6),

        id bigint generated by default as identity,
        shipping_address_id bigint,
        updated_at timestamp(6),
        user_id bigint not null,
        order_number varchar(255) not null unique,
        status varchar(255) not null check (status in ('PENDING','CONFIRMED','SHIPPED','DELIVERED','CANCELLED')),

        primary key (id)
